result.name: Tsong Long Ting

reviews.text:
Watching a concert in the Hong Kong Coliseum facilitated a food hunting tour in Hung Hom. Tsong Long Ting is a popular local Shanghai restaurant, I visited to try out their signature noodles.

This Braised Noodles with Diced Chicken was served in milky soup which was really delicious! It’s not salty at all and very enjoyable to drink or have noodles with.

And the noodles brought back so many childhood memories, as my grandma used to cook this type of noodles for me.

It’s a big bowl of noodles with yummy diced chicken and vegetables. Very affordable and filling. Would definitely like to visit again to try out other Shanghai noodles!

Tiny Shanghai style noodle place with only 5 tables.  As space is limited, customers are expected to share their table with others. 
The noodles are pretty tasty, but prices seem slightly high.
Freshly deep fried pork chop and good noodle soup. Cheap in terms of price as well!
Just good to feel yourself with delicious numerous type of dessert
